  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Automation Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in installing electrical wiring in automated machinery, including robotic systems, conveyors, and electrical control panels. </li><li>Help diagnose and resolve basic issues in electrical systems, sensors, actuators, and programmable logic controllers (PLCs) under supervision. </li><li>Perform I/O tests on automated systems to verify functionality and assist with necessary adjustments. </li><li>Maintain accurate records of cable lists, wiring diagrams, and in-process documentation. </li><li>Work closely with other electricians, engineers, and other team members to implement system improvements and upgrades. </li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirement: </strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 1 year of hands-on experience in electrical installation, preferably in an industrial or automation environment. </li><li>Familiarity with crimping, soldering, and wire stripping tools. </li><li>Ability to read and understand AC/DC electrical circuit diagrams. </li><li>Basic understanding of PLCs, sensors, and actuators is a plus. </li></ul><p><br />Please include the following information in your resume.</p><ul><li>Current & Expected Salary</li><li>Reason(s) for leaving</li><li>Notice Period / Availability to commence work</li></ul><p><br />By submitting any application or resume to us, you will be deemed to have agreed and consented to us disclosing your personal information to prospective employers for their consideration.</p><p>We regret only short-listed candidates will be notified.</p><p>EA License | 18C9251<br />Registration No | R22111484</p>",
